title: Undead Lumberjack

properties.name: description
properties.value: Undead Lumberjacks are found during Temple Trekking. They will spawn during the second version of the broken bridge event. When spawning, they continuously spawn in groups of 5 and come out of the water one by one. After a group has spawned it takes about 30 seconds for the next group to spawn. Should a clothing piece not drop, a new undead lumberjack will spawn shortly after one is killed. Only one unique drop will be dropped per trip. It is, however, possible to get multiple pieces from one event if multiple lumberjacks are killed at the same time. A Dragon halberd special attack is a good option to kill more at once. Barrages work too. They do not give any combat experience.

Undead Lumberjacks are found during Temple Trekking. They will spawn during the second version of the broken bridge event. When spawning, they continuously spawn in groups of 5 and come out of the water one by one. After a group has spawned it takes about 30 seconds for the next group to spawn. Should a clothing piece not drop, a new undead lumberjack will spawn shortly after one is killed. Only one unique drop will be dropped per trip. It is, however, possible to get multiple pieces from one event if multiple lumberjacks are killed at the same time. A Dragon halberd special attack is a good option to kill more at once. Barrages work too. They do not give any combat experience.

'''Undead Lumberjacks''' are found during [[Temple Trekking]]. They will spawn during the second version of the broken bridge event. When spawning, they continuously spawn in groups of 5 and come out of the water one by one. After a group has spawned it takes about 30 seconds for the next group to spawn. Should a clothing piece not drop, a new undead lumberjack will spawn shortly after one is killed. Only one unique drop will be dropped '''per trip'''. It is, however, possible to get multiple pieces from one event if multiple lumberjacks are killed at the same time. A [[Dragon halberd]] special attack is a good option to kill more at once. Barrages work too. They do not give any combat experience.
